<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Mercenary 1.65 Team Lead Report -=DRAFT=-</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>OVERVIEW</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Mercenaries are perceived as a fairly complete class that mostly suffers an identity crisis. This is true only because Mercenaries mature with Realm Ranks. The increased desirability of Mercenaries in RvR groups has more to do with access to powerful cheap RA's than because of the class's function. Continuing to have to rely on these cheap, very effective RA's to define our role is an undesired situation. Mercenaries need unique effective tools that allows us to fulfil our role regardless of Realm Rank or balancing actions to RA's.<br>
The only changes to Mercenaries in 1.65 came in the form of tweaks to the Crush style list. The change to Bludgeon was well received. It is too early to pass judgement on the changes to Concussion &amp; Bone Crusher.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>CONCERNS</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The Role of the Light Tank. In 1.62, Light Tanks were defined as positional fighters, or assist tanks. In this regard, Mercenaries suffer an identity crisis since very few of our tools are tailored to achieve this. Our Dual Wield spec line appears to be nothing more than another base style list. The few styles that fit our role suffer penalties that make its usefulness questionable, given other options in our base style lists. See Specline Issues below.<br>
<br>
Pure Tank Realm Abilities. It is access to these Realm Abilities (RA's) that is giving Mercenaries a rise in popularity. The Prevent Flight RA combined with our ability to Dual Wield is unmatched in Albion. Our access to Determination, especially above level 3, further compounds the issue by ensuring we're able to be in position to Prevent Flight over the course of an entire battle. If at any time these RA's are decreased in effectiveness, so will the Mercenary's role in RvR.<br>
<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>SPECLINE ISSUES</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Dual Wield:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
- This specline should reflect our new role as positional fighters or assist tanks, yet does not.<br>
<br>
- One of our positionals, Flank, suffers serious penalties due to its lack of To-Hit bonus. In PvE, the only encounters challenging enough for a full group or a larger force, will be very purple. Such high level monsters renders a no To-Hit style like Flank and its followup, ineffective. In RvR this is also seen when fighting Keep Lords. Against other players, the fluidity of a battle prevents the constant re-use of a side positional. With Flank's lack of consistancy, it is more efficient to rely on some other style to hit for less damage, more often.<br>
<br>
- The Damage vs. Endurance cost for Misty Gloom arguably makes this the worst style in this spec line.<br>
<br>
- Dark Tendrils was changed in 1.62 to be a Parry reactional. Given the popularity of the Reflection-&gt;Hypnotic Darkness chain for the Stun effect and Dual Shadows for the Bleed Effect, Dark Tendrils is rarely used.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Shield:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <br>
<br>
- Mercenaries who choose a hybrid configuration including shield spec are penalized for doing so. The interface to change from weapon to shield is time consuming and disliked. While a shield is equipped, the Mercenary is penalized by having unused points invested in the Dual Wield spec as well as being unable to use Dual Wield styles. Mercenaries have very little reason to wear shields since the defensive playstyle is better suited to other classes.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>CLASS ISSUES</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Charge:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
- Since the introduction of the Charge ability to Light Tanks, better forms of Endurance Regen. as well as Endurance Potions have been introduced to the game. This ability is now nearly redundant since groups with a source of End. Regen nearly always travel with sprint active, which is the equivalent of an unlimited Charge ability. For the Mercenary in a group without End. Regen., the ability is still rendered useless if the opponent has End. Regen. OR if the opponent uses an End. Potion. The opponent can continue sprinting long after the 10 seconds from Charge have elapsed and not worry about Mercenaries catching up since Charge offers no speed increase.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Dirty Tricks:</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
- This ability is highly situational as well as completely ineffective against 17 of 39 classes in the game.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>I'll be leaving out DT resists this report.  I did some very quick prelim testing while gathering data for Evade rates, and I'd be contradicting myself if I posted the results and claimed resist rates were low  Need to figure out what combination of buffs/SC armor/etc causes high resist rates.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>OTHER ISSUES</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- Void needs to be replaced by a worthwhile RA<br>
- Mercenaries question why we do not gain access to the Avoid Pain RA.<br>
- It has been confirmed that Evade I does not scale equally compared to higher levels of Evade when enhanced by buffs.<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>I have Danyan's logs and I've been trying to do my own testing, but I'm finding that even 400 attack rounds is not enough to minimize variance to an acceptable margin.  Basically so far, I've found that Mercenary Evade rates unbuffed is approximately 10% and doesn't change with buffs.  Minstrel evade rates unbuffed is 11% and I'm working on the buffed logs.</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>DOCUMENTATION ISSUES</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
- When Dirty Tricks is activated, the Mercenary doesn't get any message.  It should state something along the lines of &quot;You pick up an handful of dirt!&quot;<br>
- When Dirty Tricks procs, there is no message.  It should state something along the lines of &quot;You throw dirt at XXX's eyes!&quot;. <p>Kerrec Snowmane<br>
